    "question_id": "MH_002",
    "question": "How do different text processing techniques and data handling methods affect the development and application of machine learning models in tasks such as language translation, sentiment analysis, and recommendation systems?",
    "gold_answer": "Text processing techniques like tokenization and preprocessing are crucial for preparing data for machine learning models, as seen in both language translation tasks and sentiment analysis. Tokenization, whether at the word or character level, determines how text is broken down and influences model performance. For instance, in language translation between English and French, preprocessing steps such as converting text to lowercase and handling punctuation are essential for effective sentence pair alignment. In sentiment analysis of IMDb reviews, the data is labeled to distinguish positive from negative sentiments, requiring careful reading and processing of text sequences. Meanwhile, recommendation systems, such as those using the MovieLens dataset, rely on sequence-aware data handling to predict user preferences based on past behavior. These methods illustrate the importance of tailored data processing and handling in various machine learning applications.",
