    "question_id": "MH_022",
    "question": "How do convolutional operations and architectural choices across different models, such as textCNN and fully convolutional networks, illustrate the flexibility and utility of convolutional layers in handling diverse data types and tasks?",
    "gold_answer": "Convolutional layers demonstrate their versatility through various applications and architectural choices, such as in textCNN and fully convolutional networks. In textCNN, one-dimensional convolutions combined with max-over-time pooling are used to transform sequences of token representations into features for natural language processing tasks, showing how convolutional operations can capture local features in sequential data. Fully convolutional networks, on the other hand, utilize two-dimensional convolutions to extract spatial features from images, transforming these features with $1 \\times 1$ convolutions and transposed convolutions to maintain spatial resolution and output class predictions per pixel. Batch normalization is applied per-channel in convolutional layers, which helps maintain translation invariance, a critical property for both image and text data processing. Padding and stride choices further illustrate how convolutional layers can be adapted to maintain input dimensions or reduce resolution, optimizing for computational efficiency and model performance.",
