    "question": "How do affine transformations and linear models relate to training deep learning models like NiN and Softmax Regression, and how does Gaussian Process inference provide an alternative approach?",
    "gold_answer": "Affine transformations are fundamental in linear models and softmax regression, where they map inputs to outputs through linear transformations with added bias. Linear models require multiple outputs, each corresponding to an affine function, as seen in the calculation of output probabilities for classification tasks. In deep learning, models like NiN and Softmax Regression are trained on datasets like Fashion-MNIST, utilizing optimizers and specific architectures to improve accuracy. Gaussian Process inference, while initially used for regression in a closed form, offers an alternative by providing a probabilistic approach to model predictions, useful for integrating with neural networks and tackling non-Gaussian likelihoods in more complex scenarios.",
