    "question": "How does the concept of integration relate to the construction of neural network architectures and the validation of machine learning models?",
    "gold_answer": "Integration is a mathematical concept used to compute areas and volumes, and it is fundamental in understanding the behavior of functions over continuous domains. In deep learning, integration can metaphorically relate to how neural network architectures are constructed and validated. The Sequential class and custom blocks like FixedHiddenMLP and NestMLP allow for flexible model construction, akin to integrating various components to form a cohesive whole. Furthermore, the validation process in machine learning, involving the computation of averaged loss and accuracy, resembles the iterative process of integration, where results are accumulated over batches to yield a comprehensive evaluation. Thus, integration serves as both a mathematical tool and a conceptual framework for understanding neural network design and evaluation.",
