    "question": "How would you implement a fine-tuned hot dog recognition model using MLPs with efficient text preprocessing and parallel computing, while optimizing the training process through stochastic gradient descent?",
    "gold_answer": "To implement a fine-tuned hot dog recognition model with MLPs, first convert raw image and text data into sequences using a preprocessing pipeline that tokenizes and indexes the data. Fine-tune a pretrained ResNet model on a hot dog dataset by adjusting the final layers to fit the new task, leveraging the power of MLPs to handle complex data transformations. Utilize stochastic gradient descent to optimize the training process by iteratively updating model weights based on small batches of data, improving convergence speed. Enhance computational performance by distributing the training workload across multiple GPUs using high-level APIs, ensuring efficient parallel execution and synchronization. This workflow integrates text data processing, model fine-tuning, optimization techniques, and parallel computing to build a robust recognition system.",
