    "question_id": "MH_051",
    "question": "How can the challenges of sequence prediction in autoregressive models be addressed by incorporating ideas from ResNeXt and handling concept shift, while ensuring efficient model initialization?",
    "gold_answer": "Sequence prediction in autoregressive models, such as predicting stock prices, relies heavily on understanding the probability distribution of historical data. This can be improved by incorporating ResNeXt's strategy of using multiple independent groups to manage the trade-off between nonlinearity and dimensionality, which helps in efficiently processing high-dimensional data. Proper initialization of model parameters, such as using normal distribution or constant values, ensures stability and faster convergence of these complex models. Additionally, handling concept shift is crucial, as the definitions and distributions of data categories can change over time, affecting the model's predictions. By synthesizing these approaches, we can build more robust and adaptable models for sequential data prediction.",
