    "gold_answer": "Data manipulation and preprocessing are foundational skills in deep learning, enabling efficient training of models like GoogleNet on datasets such as Fashion-MNIST. These skills are crucial for resizing input data, as seen when transforming images to a $96 \times 96$ resolution before training. In contrast, handling sequence data with LSTMs requires managing the internal state with gates to address the vanishing gradient problem, a challenge distinct from image data preprocessing. Moreover, self-attention mechanisms with positional encoding bring additional complexity in sequence representation, where relative position embeddings can be leveraged to enhance model performance. These diverse applications illustrate how fundamental data skills underpin varied deep learning tasks, from image classification to sequence modeling.",
