    "question_id": "MH_057",
    "question": "How do convolutional techniques from various deep learning models, such as textCNN and NiN, utilize pooling and stride to efficiently process data, and what role does bilinear interpolation play in these processes?",
    "gold_answer": "Convolutional techniques in deep learning models like textCNN and NiN use pooling and stride to efficiently process data. textCNN employs max-over-time pooling to condense information from convolutional layers, which helps in reducing overfitting when combined with dropout. NiN, on the other hand, uses global average pooling to replace fully connected layers, reducing the number of parameters and maintaining accuracy. Stride is crucial for controlling the movement of the convolution window, allowing models to downsample inputs efficiently. Bilinear interpolation, often used in transposed convolutional layers, aids in upsampling by calculating new pixel values based on surrounding pixels, which is essential for scaling feature maps. Together, these techniques optimize the processing and transformation of input data across different models.",
