    "gold_answer": "The computational demands of deep learning models escalate as we move from simpler models, such as multilayer perceptrons, to more complex architectures like convolutional neural networks and sequence models. Implementing multilayer perceptrons can be messy due to parameter management, but they represent the foundational complexity of neural networks. Convolutional networks add further complexity by incorporating multiple channels, requiring more sophisticated data handling and computational power. Sequence models, particularly in language tasks, necessitate the evaluation of joint probabilities over sequences, adding another layer of computational intensity. These increasing demands make GPUs the preferred choice over CPUs, as they provide the necessary performance boost for training deep networks efficiently. As models grow in complexity, cloud-based solutions become viable to handle the escalating resource requirements.",
